'''Omar Federico Alderete Fernández''' (born 26 December 1996) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Sunderland AFC|Sunderland]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]]. Mainly a [[centre-back]], he can also play as a [[left-back]].<ref name="Soccerway profile">{{Soccerway|omar-alderete/290235}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Alderete began his career with [[Cerro Porteño]], he played for their U20s at the [[2016 U-20 Copa Libertadores]] between January and February 2016 where he scored one goal (vs. [[Club Bolívar|Bolívar]]) in three games.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/><ref name="BDFA profile">{{cite news|title=Omar Alderete profile|url=http://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugadores-OMAR-FEDERICO-ALDERETE-107506.html|access-date=20 February 2018|work=BDFA|date=20 February 2018}}</ref> Months later, in May 2016, Alderete made his professional debut for the club in a [[Paraguayan Primera División]] loss to [[Club Rubio Ñu|Rubio Ñu]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In his third league appearance, he scored his first senior goal in an away win versus [[Club Guaraní|Guaraní]] on 31 July.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In August 2017, Alderete joined [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Club de Gimnasia y Esgrima La Plata|Gimnasia y Esgrima]] on loan.<ref name="Joined Gimnasia y Esgrima 1">{{cite news|title=Nuevo lobo|url=http://www.tigosports.com.py/paraguayos/omar-alderete-firmo-por-gimnasia-y-esgrima|access-date=20 February 2018|work=Tigo Sports|date=3 August 2017}}</ref><ref name="Joined Gimnasia y Esgrima 2">{{cite news|title=Omar Alderete dejó Cerro y firmó por Gimnasia|url=http://d10.paraguay.com/omar-alderete-dejo-cerro-y-firmo-gimnasia-n640442|access-date=20 February 2018|work=D10|date=4 August 2017}}</ref> His first appearance came in a 4–4 draw with [[Defensa y Justicia]] on 26 August.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

===Huracán and Basel===
After one goal in twenty-two matches for Gimnasia y Esgrima, Alderete completed a transfer to [[Club Atlético Huracán|Huracán]] at the conclusion of his loan spell.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

On 4 June 2019, Alderete agreed a move to [[Swiss Super League]] outfit [[FC Basel|Basel]]; with the deal officially going through on 11 June.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2019/20-Omar Alderete">{{cite web | first = | last = FC Basel 1893 | author-link = | date = 4 June 2019 | url = https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2019/06/der-fcb-verpflichtet-omar-alderete/ | title = Der FC Basel 1893 verpflichtet Omar Alderete | format = | work = FC Basel 1893 signs Omar Alderete | publisher = FC Basel 1893 AG | language = de | access-date = 2019-06-04}}</ref> Alderete joined Basel's first team for their [[2019–20 FC Basel season]] under head coach [[Marcel Koller]]. After playing in five test games, Alderete played his domestic league debut for the club in the away game in the [[Stade Tourbillon]] on 19 July 2019 as Basel won 4–1 against [[FC Sion]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2018/20">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 19 July 2019 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31402 | title = FC Sion - FC Basel 1:4 (1:1) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2021-11-16}}</ref> He scored his first goal for his team four days later, on 23 July 2019, in the away game in the [[Philips Stadion]] in the second qualifying round of the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League]]. But this could not help the team, as Basel were defeated 2–3 by [[PSV Eindhoven]], who scored two goals in the last minutes of the game.<ref name="fcb-achiv-UCL-2019/20-PSV-FCB">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 23 July 2019 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31438 | title = PSV Eindhoven - FC Basel 3:2 (1:1) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2021-11-16}}</ref>

Alderete left the club during the transfer window of the next season. During his short period with the club Alderete played a total of 64 games for Basel scoring a total of four goals. 31 of these games were in the [[Swiss Super League]], six in the [[Swiss Cup]], four in the Champions League, 13 in the Europa League and 10 were friendly games. He scored two goals in the domestic league, one in the Swiss Cup and one in the Champions League.<ref name="fcb-achiv-Omar Alderete">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | authorlink = | year = 2020 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/spieler?command=detail&id=9989 | title = Omar Alderete - FCB statistic | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | accessdate = 2021-11-16}}</ref>

===Hertha BSC===
On 5 October 2020, Alderete signed a long-term deal with [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.herthabsc.com/de/nachrichten/2012/11/1511-_x0022_hertha-gehort-in-die-erste-liga_x0022_ |title=Omar Alderete signs for Hertha |website=Hertha BSC |date=5 October 2020 }}</ref> He made his debut in a 2–1 debut at the [[Red Bull Arena (Leipzig)|Red Bull Arena]] against [[RB Leipzig]] on 24 October.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> On 12 July 2021, Alderete signed with [[Valencia CF]] on a season-long loan with the option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 July 2021 |title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT {{!}} OMAR ALDERETE |url=https://www.valenciacf.com/en/article/en-official-statement-omar-alderete-2021-07-12 |access-date=19 August 2022 |website=www.valenciacf.com}}</ref>

===Getafe===
On 19 August 2022, Alderete joined [[Getafe CF|Getafe]] on loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 August 2022 |title=Comunicado Oficial{{!}} Alderete |url=http://www.getafecf.com/Noticia/tabid/137/Article/8427/Comunicado-Oficial-Alderete.aspx |access-date=19 August 2022 |website=Getafe CF |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220819122323/http://www.getafecf.com/Noticia/tabid/137/Article/8427/Comunicado-Oficial-Alderete.aspx |archive-date=19 August 2022}}</ref> On 25 May of the following year, he signed a permanent five-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getafecf.com/noticias/comunicado-oficial-omar-alderete|title=Comunicado Oficial {{!}} Alderete|trans-title=Official announcement {{!}} Alderete|publisher=Getafe CF|language=es|date=25 May 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023}}</ref>

===Sunderland===
On 12 August 2025, [[Premier League]] side [[Sunderland A.F.C|Sunderland]] announced the signing of Alderete on a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.safc.com/news/2025/august/12/omar-alderete-signs-four-year-deal/|title=Omar Alderete signs four-year deal|publisher=Sunderland AFC|date=12 August 2025|accessdate=12 August 2025}}</ref> On 27 September, he scored his first goal for the club in a 1–0 away victory over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the Premier League.

==International career==
Alderete has represented Paraguay at [[Paraguay men's national under-17 football team|U17]], [[Paraguay men's national under-20 football team|U20]] and [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|U23]] level.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> He won eight caps for the U17 team at the [[2013 South American Under-17 Football Championship]] in Argentina, prior to winning seven caps for the U20s at the [[2015 South American Youth Football Championship]] in Uruguay.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In May 2016, Alderete played four times for the U23s at the [[2016 Toulon Tournament]] in France, scoring one goal in a win over Guinea on 19 May.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> He was called up to train with [[Juan Carlos Osorio]]'s [[Paraguay national football team|senior squad]] in 2018.<ref name="Paraguayan Football Association">{{cite news|title=Osorio llamó a los del exterior|url=http://www.apf.org.py/n/osorio-llamo-a-los-del-exterior|access-date=26 September 2018|work=Paraguayan Football Association|date=25 September 2018|archive-date=3 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221203033439/https://www.apf.org.py/n/osorio-llamo-a-los-del-exterior|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut for them on 20 November 2018 in a friendly against [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]]; as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/lineups?gameId=528270|title=South Africa v Paraguay game report|date=20 November 2018}}</ref>

